        <p>This tells Flare that, unless otherwise directed, all topics will use the template page you selected. But if you want to use a second template page, you can open the Properties dialog for a particular topic and point to a different template page. In that case, the template page set in the target is typically the one that the majority of your topics will use.  But for the other topic(s) using a different template page, you can override the target setting. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Flare/Template-Pages/Process/Associating-Template-Pages-Topics1.htm">Associating Template Pages With Topics</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
    </body>
</html>